
#  Workshop App

This is a workshop app built using the MERN stack (MongoDB, Express, React, and Node.js) with the Mongoose library for object modeling. The app provides a simple interface for adding, updating, deleting, and retrieving workshop data.

Installation
To run the app locally, follow these steps:

Clone the repository to your local machine.
Install dependencies by running npm install in the root directory.
Start the server by running npm start in the root directory.
Navigate to http://localhost:3000 in your browser to view the app.
Usage
The app provides a simple interface for adding, updating, deleting, and retrieving workshop data. Users can perform the following actions:

Add a workshop
To add a new workshop, click on the "Add Workshop" button on the homepage. Fill out the form with the required information and click "Submit". The new workshop will be added to the database and displayed on the homepage.

Update a workshop
To update an existing workshop, click on the "Edit" button next to the workshop you wish to update. Make the necessary changes to the form and click "Submit". The workshop will be updated in the database and the homepage will be refreshed to display the updated workshop.

Delete a workshop
To delete an existing workshop, click on the "Delete" button next to the workshop you wish to delete. The workshop will be removed from the database and the homepage will be refreshed to remove the deleted workshop.

Retrieve workshops
To retrieve all workshops, simply navigate to the homepage. The app will display all workshops currently stored in the database.

Technologies Used
The app was built using the following technologies:

MongoDB - a NoSQL database used to store workshop data
Mongoose - a MongoDB object modeling library used to interface with the database
Express - a web application framework for Node.js used to build the server-side of the app
React - a JavaScript library used to build the client-side of the app
Node.js - a JavaScript runtime used to build the server-side of the app

Future Improvements
Some possible improvements for the app include:

Adding user authentication to restrict access to workshop data
Improving the UI design to make it more user-friendly
Adding a search feature to allow users to search for workshops by keyword or location




